{
  "texts": [
    "First, we used TAACO (version 2.0.4, Crossley et al. (2019)) to build predictive classifiers.",
    "Operationally, TAACO is a cohesion measurement tool, which calculates 150 indices.",
    "TAACO reported on a variety of validated local and global features of cohesion (Crossley et al. 2019), which methodologically aligns with LLMs-surprisals of degree expressions at the target word and the sentence level.",
    "TAACO indices can be classified into three types: (i) type-token ratio indices (ttr, including specific parts of speech, lemmas, bigrams, trigrams and more), (ii) adjacent overlap indices (at both the sentence and paragraph level), and (iii) connectives indices.",
    "For type (i), we examined the number of unique lemmas (types) divided by the number of total running lemmas (tokens) (\"lemma_ttr\"), and Number of unique bigram lemmas (types) divided by the number of total bigram lemmas (tokens) (\"bigram_lemma_ttr\")."
  ]
}